        "created_at": "2026-01-06T15:46:30.525Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I have noticed what I feel is a bug that began a few versions ago. When I close Signal (by backing out of the program, not just minimizing) and then I go back in, it opens on the last chat I was in regardless of why I\u2019m going in. So if someone texts me and I get a notification and I open Signal it will go to the last chat I was in regardless of the fact that I just received a text in a different chat. It always defaults to opening in the last chat you were in.</p>\n<p>Previously if I closed Signal properly it would open to the main window so I could see all chats. Then I could click on who I wanted to click on. The only way I have found around this is if I hit the hamburger on the bottom right and click \u201cclear all\u201d programs currently running.</p>\n<p>Is there a way around this to restore previous behavior? Is this a new \u201cfeature\u201d because I see it as a bug.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 16,
