        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/ccd318/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-06T17:40:07.432Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Sentinel\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"74068\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/fbc32d/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Sentinel:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The only way I have found around this is if I hit the hamburger on the bottom right and click \u201cclear all\u201d programs currently running.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Does it also return to the chat overview if you close the app by swiping it out of your recent apps? If the app is just closed with the gesture or home button, it\u2019s still running in the background, so this would be expected behaviour. Swiping it away from the app overview should have the same effect as the hamburger (stopping apps that are running in the background), except it only applies to that one app.</p>",
