        "cooked": "<p>desert_nip</p>\n<p>I guess I\u2019m not explaining it right. I use the \u201cthree button navigation\u201d on android so when I exit signal I did it by clicking the left button (triangle) and (before this started) that used to be good enough to \u201cexit out\u201d of the app. Next time I opened it it opened to the main screen showing all chats. Now when I do that it doesn\u2019t close. It opens on the last chat I was in. If I press the right button (a square) then it shows all apps that I used since the last time I \u201ccleared\u201d them. Yes, I can swipe just that one app that works. Closes it out I guess but that was not needed before.</p>\n<p>Herohtar,</p>\n<p>I am running version 7.68.5 and it still does the same thing.</p>",
