        "name": "",
        "username": "Sentinel",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/fbc32d/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2026-02-13T22:58:29.840Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I think I might have figured out the problem, or at least what it is related to. I did a factory reset on my phone to see if it fixed the problem. It did. So then I set about trying to find out what setting I change that effects it. I think I found it.</p>\n<p>On my phone I have the developer options turned on. The specific option that I believe to be the culprit is \u201cDon\u2019t Keep Activities\u201d. Oddly this setting is supposed to do exactly the opposite of what is happening. It is supposed to close apps as I \u201cleave\u201d them. And it does, for all other apps. And it used to for Signal too, until recently.</p>\n<p>So I\u2019m not sure but if correct then Signal must have changed something in a recent release that conflicts with that setting causing it to do the opposite of the intended action.</p>",
